Customer Journey and Workflow

Current State

 

The long-tail segment receives no structured outreach before the 60 day-window (see exec summary for additional detail). At-risk accounts are identified by gut instinct at renewal time. Service delivery issues that damage customer sentiment months before renewal are typically discovered at T-60,  too late to remediate.

The renewals typically fill during quarterly cohorts: 1/1, 4/1, 7/1 (largest), 10/1.

 

When customers are most at risk of churn:

Service delivery issues that went unresolved and surface at renewal

Contact has changed and outreach reaches the wrong person

No proactive communication in the preceding 90+ days

Federal/state government procurement cycles (e.g., state of New York, California) that require months of lead time



