Most Impactful Workflows for the Agent

•  T-180 early outreach  initiate the conversation before the compressed reactive window. Brad  specifically identified this as the highest-value intervention.

•  Structured multi-touch email cadence  ensuring 100% methodology compliance across all ~1,500 accounts

•  Inbound response handling  consistent automated responses to routine questions (billing, service delivery, OEM coverage, pricing, FAQs) to free team capacity

•  Escalation routing  categorize inbound responses and route to the correct team (Sales, Pricing, Legal, Billing, Service) based on question type

•  Automated activity logging to Salesforce timeline  replacing the current manual email-upload-to-files workflow

 

Internal Change Management

•  Team behavioral shift from reactive to proactive posture  leadership alignment needed before launch

•  Manual email-upload-to-Salesforce-files workflow will be superseded by automated timeline logging  training required

•  Customer service team has never used Gainsight  any Gainsight-based dashboards or logging will require onboarding

•  Sales rep CC workflow: today sales is only CC’d on sub-$20k renewals when the team can’t reach a contact. Future state is a summary dashboard or account-level digest  not individual CC on every email thread (to be confirmed).

 







