Section 4: Agent Authority and Boundaries

This section defines what the Agent is authorized to do on behalf of your team, and where human judgment is required. Items marked [x] reflect what was discussed or confirmed on March 9, 2026. We’ll review and finalize remaining items together.

 

What the Agent Will Do

[x]  Send proactive emails to customers

[ ]  Make proactive phone calls (voice channel not yet confirmed for REMI segment)

[x]  Answer FAQs from your knowledge base (high priority given broad domain  scope to be confirmed with Taylor’s FAQ materials)

[x]  Share standard documentation (renewal agreements, policy details)

[x]  Provide non-sensitive account information (policy details, renewal dates, agreement summaries)

[x]  Guide customers through standard renewal processes

[x]  Schedule follow-up interactions

[ ]  Update CRM records (automated Salesforce timeline logging is desired, technical feasibility to be confirmed)

[x] Route equipment add requests to sales (NSA@theremigroup.com)

[x] Forward POs to Account Services for registration

[x] Send renewal confirmations upon PO receipt





 

What the Agent Will NOT Do

[x] Negotiate pricing or offer discounts

[x] Modify contract terms or coverage

[x] Make product roadmap commitments

[x] Handle payment or billing transactions (direct to billing@theremigroup.com)

[x] Access sensitive financial data

[x] Process refunds or delete customer data

[x] Approve back-dates >1 month or large deletes >$10K

[x] Send renewals for exception accounts without reviewing exception list



