Customer nuance that should be considered out of scope for MVP:

New York State accounts: 90-day notice required for non-renewals; price increases cannot be applied without manager sign-off; auto-renewals sent 45 days prior (not 30)

New York City accounts: same 90-day non-renewal notice; contract number and discount percentage must appear on renewal

NYS Downstate: subject line must include vendor name, prior PO number, department, and term dates; Excel version required alongside PDF

USPI: written approval required to register; specific contracting vehicle required

State of NC: prior PO number required in subject line

Ohio State University: renewals submitted via eStores portal, not email

State of Indiana: equipment schedule broken out by department, sent to individual contacts

Kansas State University: broken out by department, individual item-level contacts

Indiana University: broken out by location, sent to each department head

Duke University: requires SOW and EMA attached to every renewal

Case Western Reserve University: requires EMA attached to every renewal

San Luis Obispo Surgery Center: requires signature portion on renewals

Excedr: no increases if no losses; valid increases capped at 5%

CNA accounts (CWS prefix): sent to CNA rep, not the customer

K-12 accounts: wall-to-wall coverage, managed by Kyle Hornick

Accounts with unique contact routing:

Mass General Brigham (Dept PPM): specific email addresses only

Sonic Healthcare USA / Certified Group: must loop in Kyle Hornik

Surgical Care Affiliates / SCA: must loop in Kiernan Joyce

NYC Health & Hospitals battery quotes: three specific contacts required on every quote



⚠  Note: No unique identifier currently links REMI Salesforce, Polaris, the Access database, and Gainsight CS. The policy/agreement number in Salesforce opportunities is a candidate mapping key to Polaris records. Annual premium values and living policy changes (adds/deletes) are in Polaris only. The MVP will use a flat file approach. Elana Weinbaum raised concern about any integration that creates rework post-tech transformation; the flat file MVP approach is designed to be transformation-safe.

 

 

